  "doc_id": "36357",
  "text": "Nrg1 is a growth factor known to be important in many bodily systems, including the nervous system. Nrg1 functions are largely mediated by the receptor tyrosine kinases ErbB2, 3 and 4. ErbB4 has been indicated as the predominant receptor for Nrg1 [CITATION_1] . Recently, Nrg1/erbB4 signaling has been highlighted to have a crucial role in the control of cortical development of GABA circuitry, and erbB4 has been specifically localised to the postsynaptic density of glutamatergic synapses contacting the dendrites of inhibitory neurons [CITATION_2] . Deficits in GABAergic interneurons, particularly parvalbumincontaining basket and chanderlier cells, is one of the most salient features of schizophrenia.",
